        <div class="ld-section" style="text-align:center;">
            <div class="ld-label-light">Free Interactive Preview</div>
            <h2 style="color:#fff;">See and hear the system before you buy</h2>
            <p style="color:#b0c4de; max-width:640px; margin:0 auto 12px;">The free interactive app lets you <strong style="color:#fff;">experience the Rhythm Library System in action</strong> before purchasing the book. Select a pattern group, set your tempo, and hear how the sticking patterns flow against the rhythm sequence.</p>
            <p style="color:#b0c4de; max-width:640px; margin:0 auto 32px;">This is not just a demo — it is a <strong style="color:#fff;">fully working practice tool</strong> you can use alongside the book every time you sit down at the kit.</p>
            <div class="ld-steps">
                <div class="ld-step"><div class="ld-step-num">1</div><h3>Choose a Page</h3><p>Select a rhythm exercise like Three Camps to load the notation sequence.</p></div>
                <div class="ld-step"><div class="ld-step-num">2</div><h3>Choose a Pattern</h3><p>Pick a GK 16ths sticking pattern and see the drum notation in real time.</p></div>
                <div class="ld-step"><div class="ld-step-num">3</div><h3>Play &amp; Practice</h3><p>Press Play or click any single measure to loop it at your tempo.</p></div>
            </div>
            <button class="ld-btn-primary" style="font-size:1.05rem; padding:16px 40px;" @onclick='() => Nav.NavigateTo("/")'>Launch the Free App</button>
        </div>
