    <!-- About the Author -->
    <div class="ld-gray">
        <div class="ld-section">
            <div class="ld-label">About the Author</div>
            <h2>Gordy Knudtson — World-Class Drummer &amp; Educator</h2>
            <div class="ld-author-grid">
                <div class="ld-author-bio">
                    <p>Gordy Knudtson is a professional drummer, educator, and author with one of the most distinguished careers in modern drumming. He served as the drummer for the <strong>Steve Miller Band for more than thirty years</strong> — joining in 1987 and performing with them through 2021, including their induction into the <strong>Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2016</strong>.</p>
                    <p>Throughout his career Gordy has collaborated with Booker T. &amp; the MGs, jazz pianist Ben Sidran, guitarist Roy Buchanan, and Cuban pianist Nachito Herrera. He began drumming at age 15 and turned professional at 17.</p>
                    <p>As an educator, Gordy headed the <strong>Percussion Department at McNally Smith College</strong> in St. Paul, Minnesota. He also pioneered the development of <strong>Open/Close Technique</strong> — published in Percussive Notes Magazine and presented at PASIC 2003 alongside drum legends Joe Morello and Jim Chapin. Ed Shaughnessy described it as <em>"an historically important form of technique that ranks with the Moeller system."</em></p>
                </div>
                <div class="ld-author-sidebar">
                    <div class="ld-highlights-card">
                        <div class="ld-highlights-title">Career Highlights</div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>🎸 Steve Miller Band — 30+ years</li>
                            <li>🏆 Rock &amp; Roll Hall of Fame 2016</li>
                            <li>🎓 McNally Smith College — Dept. Head</li>
                            <li>🥁 Booker T. &amp; the MGs</li>
                            <li>🎹 Ben Sidran — 6 years</li>
                            <li>📖 Open/Close Technique pioneer</li>
                            <li>🎵 PASIC 2003 featured artist</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <a class="ld-bio-link" href="https://www.gk-music.com/gordy-knudtson/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Full Bio at gk-music.com ↗</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
